	<p>
		Hi, I’m Abdi (Abdurakhmon). I am an Electrical Engineering undergraduate at the University of Debrecen, originally from Uzbekistan.
	</p>

	<p>
		My focus is learning how to bridge the gap between software systems (IT) and industrial hardware (OT). My background is a mix of academic theory and hands-on electrical grid experience. Recently, I worked at Regional Electric Power Networks (HET.UZ), where I helped monitor 110kV telemetry via SCADA and validated Siemens S7-1200 PLC logic for automatic transfer switches.
	</p>

	<p>
		Rather than just reading textbooks, I spend my free time building HIL simulations. I build these to understand real-time control logic, deal with physical hardware constraints, and prepare for a career in automotive automation—with the ultimate long-term goal of working in F1.
	</p>

	<h4>The Tech Stack I Actually Use</h4>
	<p>I am currently building projects and solving problems using the following tools:</p>

	<p><strong>Hardware & Industrial (OT):</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Siemens TIA Portal (S7-1200, LAD/FBD)</li>
		<li>SCADA / HMI Systems</li>
		<li>CODESYS (SoftPLC)</li>
		<li>IEC 61131-3 (Structured Text & Ladder Logic)</li>
		<li>AutoCAD Electrical</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Software & Scripting (IT):</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Python (Physics modeling, data visualization, Modbus scripting)</li>
		<li>C/C++ (Object-Oriented Programming)</li>
		<li>MATLAB / Simulink</li>
	</ul>

